fielddes: No. of legal entities associated with building unit address
City name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
5-digit zip code of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Lattitude of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that states "Yes" if the building unit address is verified to be deliverable based on the Delivery Point Validation Process of USPS.

The Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) is a 5-digit numeric code which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the building unit address lies according to USPS.
Metro or Micro Type classification of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) in which the building unit address lies according to USPS.
Delivery Point Validation (DPV) Match Code of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Information related to the delivery point validation of this address.
Enhanced Line of Travel for the building unit address.
The neighborhood, or city subdivision; used with Puerto Rican addresses.
Directional information after a street name (N, SW, etc.) of building unit address.
Correction character, or check digit, for the 11-digit barcode
Indicator that equals 1 if unit information present for all or for some of the Organization and 0 otherwise.
Country name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Name of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which building unit address lies according to USPS.
Congressional disctrict name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Numerical portion (if any) of the 2nd line of the building unit address, such as a unit or suite number. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicates the precision of the latitude and longitude values.
Indicates which changes were made to the input address.
Indicates the number of hours the time zone is offset from Universal Time Coordinated (UTC) for building unit address.
Indicates that a delivery point was active in the past, but is currently vacant (in most cases, unoccupied over 90 days) and is not receiving deliveries.
Description of the building unit address type within a campus
The default city name for this 5-digit ZIP Code
Unique ID given to the building unit.
Unique ID given to the building. (refering building address)
Type of the building associated with the building unit: Multi Unit or Single Unit
No. of organizations associated with building unit address
Indicator that equals 1 if an agent active at building unit address and 0 otherwise.
First line of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
9-digit zip code of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Zip code classification of the building unit address stating whether it is a P.O. Box or not. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Country code of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
RDI indicates whether the building unit address is Residential, Commercial, P.O. Box or Unknown based on USPS reporting.
Longitude of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicates if mailers can sort their mailings by line of travel sequence (A-Ascending, D-Descending).
Indicates the common name of the time zone associated with the building unit address.
Early warning system flag; a positive result indicates the street of the building unit address is not yet ready for mail delivery.
Indicates whether there is a building unit address match in the LACSLink database.
The house, PO Box, or building number
The name of the street
Directional information before a street name (N, SW, etc.) of building unit address.
Describes building unit address within a complex/building (Ste, Apt, etc.)
Descriptive information about the building unit address of a building within a campus
The private mailbox number, assigned by a CMRA
The 4-digit add-on code (more specific than 5-digit ZIP)

The last two digits of the house/box number, unless an "H" record is matched, in which case this is the secondary unit number representing the delivery point information to form the delivery point barcode (DPBC).
City, state, and ZIP Code combined
No. of locations associated with building unit address
Indicator that equals 1 if the building unit address is valid based on a match with the USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
Second line of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State's abbrivated name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State name of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County-level Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) Code of the building unit address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that equals 1 if the building unit address is valid based on USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
The name of the person or company at this building unit address. Very rarely, this field might be filled automatically based on the USPS address record.
Describes steps taken to verify and standardize the address and other information about it.
This field will contain additional information about the building unit address.
Indicates the type of record that was matched. Only given if a DPV match is made.
The postal carrier route for the building unit address
Indicates if the time zone "obeys," or, in other words, adjusts their clocks forward and back with the seasons. (True or Null).
Indicates whether the building unit address is associated with a Commercial Mail Receiving Agency (CMRA), also known as a private mailbox (PMB) operator.
The reason code for the LACSLink indication for the building unit address.

Indicator indicates a match (or not) to the USPS SuiteLink data. SuiteLink attempts to provide secondary information such as "suite" or "apartment" whenever there is a match based on address and company name.
Indicator that equals 1 if the building unit address is active based on USPS address verification and 0 otherwise.
Abbreviated value describing the street (St, Ave, Blvd, etc.) of building unit address.
Private mailbox unit designator, assigned by a CMRA
